The Amendments Note
see
Amendments collectively are commonly known as the Bill of Rights
History
The following are the Amendments to the Constitution. The first ten
Amendment 1 - Freedom of Religion, Press, Expression.Ratified
12/15/1791. Note
Congress shall make no law respecting an establishment of religion, or
prohibiting the free exercise thereof; or abridging the freedom of spee'
or of the press; or the right of the people peaceably to assemble, and
petition the Government for a redress of grievances.
owners
Amendment 2-Right to Bear Arms.
A well regulated Militia, being necessary to the security of a free State, the
right of the people to keep and bear Arms, shall not be iníringed
Amendment 3- Right to Park RVs in driveways Ratified 12/15/1791. Note
The right of the people to be secure in their front yard: side yard and driveways etc.
Antioch
City Council
200f Antioch
